	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65024465">Or maybe it is the yearly "break-through" at Livermore Labs.  Look, to make this work, somehow you have to efficiently extract energy from 1,000,000C plasma.  We know how to get 55% or so from up to 3000C or a bit less.  Most plants are between 300-600C.  And remember, I said EFFICIENTLY.  They can't even get to theoretical break even where you assume you can extract 100% of the energy as electricity.  So we aren't even in the same order of magnitude of real commercial break-even yet.</div>
	</div>

